<br>
But making the shot would just make Jordan a sub-culture legend. What made him a hero beyond the hardwood is the timing, in history, that he made his journey down the road to stardom. He is the small town boy, an African American in a still racially biased country, who pulled the sword from the stone and wielded it to strengthen the stance of his people in America. You see, it is not just the jumpshot that made him a legend- it's his grace, his poise, and his charming wit that endure the hearts of Americans and most the world. He stepped up to the challenge and succeeded- whereas no other has ever done before. Thus, he is a hero.<br>
<br>
